
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses [set-value] to change the value of the [.result] node. It utilizes [strings.replace] to replace occurrences of a specified string within the [.result] node with the string "true". The [strings.replace] slot takes two arguments: the first is the string to be replaced, and the second is the replacement string. The code effectively updates the [.result] node by substituting all instances of the specified string with "true".
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      .:[[references]]
      .:true
